            <title>[OPENJPA-1455] SynchronizeMapping ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN fails with column already exist exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1455</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SynchronizeMapping ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN fails with column already exist exception. The failure happens when there are multiple tables with the same name but in different schema. When OpenJPA detects a missing column from one table with schema X, it tried to to add the column to another table in default schema, resulting in column already exist exception. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
